#BlackDay #JaiHind #14FebPulwamaBravehearts #IndianArmy #BlackDayForIndia

Feb 14, 2019 a suicide bomber crashes a car packed with 300kg of explosives into a convoy of  CRPF, killing more than 40 CRPF jawans and injuring at least 70. The terror attack took place in Pulwama, about 20km from Srinagar,capital of Jammu& Kashmir. #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

February 15 (Friday)Jaish-e-Mohammad claims responsibility for the bombing and also released a video in which the bomber, Adil Ahmad Dar, a 20-year-old school dropout,  said he hoped to reach heaven by means of his attack on the Indian convoy.  #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

February 16 (Saturday )India weighs options after Kashmir attack: Diplomatic isolation and military strikes discussed amid domestic pressure to respond in kind to Pulwama terror attack. #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

India hikes the customs duty to 200 per cent on all goods imported from Pakistan, following revocation of the MFN status in the aftermath of the Pulwama terror attack, Finance Minister Arun Jaitely states in a tweet. #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

February 22 (Friday)India's Union minister Nitin Gadkari says in New Delhi that India has decided to "stop" the flow of its share of water to Pakistan from rivers under the Indus Waters Treaty (IWT) after the Pulwama terror attack. #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

February 25 (Monday):India’s National Intelligency Agency (NIA) identifies vehicle used in carrying out the attack in Pulwama. “The owner of the vehicle is identified as Sajjad Bhat, who has joined Jaish-e-Mohammed terror outfit”, NIA spokesman says #14FebPulwamaBravehearts

February 26 (Tuesday)12 Indian Air Force Mirage 2000 jets drop 1,000 kg bombs on suspected Jaish-e-Mohammed camps across the Line of Control (LoC) in Balakot, Pakistan  at 3.30am.This was followed by the Pulwama attack #14FebPulwamaBravehearts
